RopVirtualProtectExecute.R9 = (DWORD64)&PreviousProtectionAttribute;

CreateTimerQueueTimer(&hTimer, hTimerQueue, (WAITORTIMERCALLBACK)NtContinue, &RopVirtualProtectExecute, 700, 0, WT_EXECUTEINTIMERTHREAD);

// Wait for all the timer queues to complete
WaitForMultipleObjects(7, &hTimer, TRUE, INFINITE);

return bFlag;
```

This code creates a new timer queue with a delay of 700 milliseconds for the VirtualProtect function (restoration). After all the timers complete, we wait for all the timers using `WaitForMultipleObjects()` and return `bFlag`. This ensures that the original protection properties of the memory block are restored after the sleep function completes.

