```

This implementation is slightly different because it checks for the "DelegateExecute" value and creates it if it doesn't exist. This is necessary because the ASCII version of RegSetKeyValue doesn't set the value size automatically like the Unicode version.

After setting the "DelegateExecute" value, the rest of the code executes the command to launch the FodHelper.exe process and cleans up the registry keys created during the UAC bypass.

