```c++
HANDLE make_new_process(HANDLE &mainThread) {
    STARTUPINFO si = { 0 };
    PROCESS_INFORMATION pi = { 0 };
    wchar_t calc_path[MAX_PATH] = { 0 };
    DWORD calc_path_len = GetSystemDirectory(calc_path, MAX_PATH);
    calc_path_len += wcslen(L"\\calc.exe");
    wcscpy(&calc_path[calc_path_len], L"\\calc.exe");

    if (!CreateProcess(NULL, calc_path, NULL, NULL, FALSE, CREATE_SUSPENDED, NULL, NULL, &si, &pi)) {
        printf("[ERROR] Failed to create process.\n");
        return INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE;
    }

    mainThread = pi.hThread;
    ResumeThread(pi.hThread);

    return pi.hProcess;
}
```

This function creates a new process for Microsoft Excel using the `CreateProcess` function with the `CREATE_SUSPENDED` flag set. This suspends the creation of the new process and allows us to set up the environment before resuming it using the `ResumeThread` function. The main thread handle of the new process is saved in the `mainThread` variable and returned to the caller.

